<p>In this podcast I cover the essence of Free Will - the central argument most philosophers muddle or sidestep. Making it really simple, the whole subject boils down to one argument, one simple choice.</p>

<p>After listening to the podcast, read the OnePageBook titled, <a href="https://isene.org/onepagebooks/#1pb-3-free-will">“Free will”</a> and the article, <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/061keir0a0hacf5/onwill.pdf?raw=1">“On Will”</a>.</p>

<center><img src="https://isene.org/assets/onepagebooks/3-freewill/cover.jpg" width="350" /></center>

<p>Then feel free to pitch in with your ideas on how free will can be proven or disproven with strict logical arguments (or even using mathematical logic).</p>

